Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Pop the potatoes onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(chopped) (stalks and all).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Cut the @tomato{2}(cut into 2cm chunks).

Season the @Irish Beef Rump{250%g} with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once the oil is hot, fry the beef until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you like it medium and a further ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, remove from the pan, cover and allow to rest.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with @butter{2%tbsp} and a drizzle of oil.

When melted, add the @prawns{180%g}, tomatoes, garlic and half the parsley.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Stir in @sugar{1/2%tsp} along with @water{25%ml}.

Season with salt and pepper and cook until tomatoes are just softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the tomatoes have started to soften, stir through the @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice) and remaining parsley.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and sugar.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Slice the beef and share between your plates.

Spoon over the tomato garlic prawns.

Serve the roast potatoes and @salad leaves{40%g} alongside.

Finish the salad with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}.